## One-Way ANOVA -- Testing if at least one chanel type has a different mean weight



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code  code-line-numbers="false"}
aov(weight_g ~ unittype, data = trout) %>% 
  tidy()
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
# A tibble: 2 × 6
  term         df    sumsq meansq statistic    p.value
  <chr>     <dbl>    <dbl>  <dbl>     <dbl>      <dbl>
1 unittype      6   58579. 9763.       109.  5.65e-134
2 Residuals 11977 1075510.   89.8       NA  NA        
```


